text: Wagga Wagga is a small city on the banks of the Murrumbidgee River in New South Wales, Australia. The name Wagga Wagga is a Wiradjuri Indigenous Australian word. Wagga Wagga means place of many dances and celebrations. Wagga Wagga has a humid subtropical climate (Cfa in the Koeppen climate classification). Wagga Wagga has passenger trains to and from Sydney. == References == ==Other websites== Category:Cities in New South Wales
